  "@id": "ocp:github/descriptinc--descript-audio-codec",
  "meta": {
    "title": "Descript Audio Codec (.dac): High-Fidelity Audio Compression with Improved RVQGAN",
    "description": "State-of-the-art audio codec with 90x compression factor. Supports 44.1kHz, 24kHz, and 16kHz mono/stereo audio.",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "dateCreated": "2026-03-22T03:07:57.811Z",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-22T03:07:57.811Z",
    "keywords": [
      "audio",
      "audio-compression",
      "codec",
      "compression-algorithm",
      "deep-learning",
      "gans",
      "generative-adversarial-network",
      "pytorch",
      "residual-vector-quantization"
    ],
    "license": "MIT"
  },
  "problemSolved": {
    "statement": "This repository contains training and inference scripts\nfor the Descript Audio Codec (.dac), a high fidelity general\nneural audio codec, introduced in the paper titled **High-Fidelity Audio Compression with Improved RVQGAN**.",
    "context": "This repository contains training and inference scripts\nfor the Descript Audio Codec (.dac), a high fidelity general\nneural audio codec, introduced in the paper titled **High-Fidelity Audio Compression with Improved RVQGAN**.\n\n![](https://static.arxiv.org/static/browse/0.3.4/images/icons/favicon-16x16.png) [arXiv Paper: High-Fidelity Audio Compression with Improved RVQGAN\n](http://arxiv.org/abs/2306.06546) <br>\n📈 [Demo Site](https://descript.notion.site/Descript-Audio-Codec-11389fce0ce2419891d6591a68f814d5)<br>\n⚙ [Model Weights](https://github.com/descriptinc/descript-audio-codec/releases/download/0.0.1/weights.pth)\n\n👉 With Descript Audio Codec, you can compress **44.1 KHz audio** into discrete codes at a **low 8 kbps bitrate**.  <br>\n🤌 That's approximately **90x compression** while maintaining exceptional fidelity and minimizing artifacts.  <br>\n💪 Our universal model works on all domains (speech, environment, music, etc.), making it widely applicable to generative modeling of all audio.  <br>\n👌 It can be used as a drop-in replacement for EnCodec for all audio language modeling applications (such as AudioLMs, MusicLMs, MusicGen, etc.) <br>\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n<img src=\"./assets/comparsion_stats.png\" alt=\"Comparison of compressions approaches. Our model achieves a higher compression factor compared to all baseline methods. Our model has a ~90x compression factor compared to 32x compression factor of EnCodec and 64x of SoundStream. Note that we operate at a target bitrate of 8 kbps, whereas EnCodec operates at 24 kbps and SoundStream at 6 kbps. We also operate at 44.1 kHz, whereas EnCodec operates at 48 kHz and SoundStream operates at 24 kHz.\" width=35%></p>",
    "cynefinDomain": "complex"
  },
